---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Blog">
  <article class="blog-container">
    <header class="blog-header">
      <h1>Gathering Figs</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A memory of Pappou and the garden</p>
    </header>
    
    <section class="content">
      <p>My feet were carefully placed in the stable crevices of the long smooth limbs of the tree; while I was normally scared of heights, the feeling of something alive supporting me gave me comfort[cite: 46, 47]. I reached forward, eyeing a fig whose plump green skin was slowly tearing away from the red and white flesh[cite: 48].</p>
      
      <p>I twisted the stem to release it from the branch, and dropped it into the basket below[cite: 49]. My Pappou, my grandfather, gave a sharp nod of approval up at me, while hooking his gnarled cane around another branch to bring it down for further inspection[cite: 50]. I listened to his advice earnestly, wanting to preserve his ways[cite: 51].</p>

      <p>When the basket was full, I gently slipped down from the tree; the red soil was laden with hay and plastered with a mush of ant-ridden figs[cite: 52, 53]. Pappou smooths the wispy white strands that barely shield his tanned bald head[cite: 54]. He picks up a fig and peels it with his fingers; the swirls and creases of his calloused hands are caked with dirt, his nails are dull and strong[cite: 55, 56].</p>

      <p>He waved me over and handed me a half. A thin white skin covered the pink flesh; it was chewy and sweet with a slight crunch from the seeds[cite: 57, 58]. I wiped my sticky fingers on my shirt, picked up the basket, and carried it up the limestone stairs, dodging the yellowjackets[cite: 59]. I wiggled free from my dusty flip flops and opened the creaky screen door[cite: 60].</p>

      <p>Some figs are destined for snacking... they always taste sweeter from her hands[cite: 62, 64]. Some figs are destined to be roughly chopped and sprinkled with sugar and spices[cite: 65]. The rest of the figs are destined to be cut in halves and organized on a long wooden board to dry and wrinkle in the sun[cite: 69]. These figs are the ones that would be nestled in our suitcase and flown back to New York[cite: 70].</p>

      <p>But I knew that it wasn't time yet to go back to New York[cite: 71]. I placed the basket on the table and rushed outside; Pappou and I had more treasures to collect from his garden[cite: 72, 73].</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .blog-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 4rem auto; background: white; padding: 4rem; border-left: 8px solid var(--ocean-blue); }
  .blog-header h1 { font-size: 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .subtitle { font-style: italic; color: var(--soft-turquoise); font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .content p { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--dark-navy); }
</style>